{
  "type": "PrimaryTheme",
  "number": 7464,
  "title": "teachers of the law",
  "comment": "Those professionally trained to develop, teach and apply the OT law. In the application of the law the oral teaching of these people often assumed greater authority than the written law. Thus, by the time of the NT, the teachers of the law were in conflict with Jesus Christ and the apostles, who taught with authority and condemned the outward religious acts that the teachers had fostered.",
  "refgroup": null,
  "children": [],
